main event: Two unidentified objects resembling bright white lights were observed for approximately 4-5 seconds over the Pacific Ocean on 17 September 1965.
interesting points: The observation was reported by military personnel,The objects were described as moving at high speed and in a straight line,One object was at a medium altitude and the other was low,The objects disappeared in less than 10 seconds,The report concluded that the observation was consistent with satellites.
witness description: military personnel at Pearl Harbor Navy Station
